subSubSection.paragraph:
Pseudopotamilla knightjonesae

sp. nov.
, differs from 

P. reniformis

from the White Sea for the following features: mid-dorsal collar margins triangular (rounded in 

P. reniformis

); ventral lappets of collar triangular, divided longitudinally by a depth incision (rounded, shallow, divided longitudinally by a short incision in 

P. reniformis

) and absence of pygidial eyes (present in 

P. reniformis

) (
Table 4
).
